# Best practices
- Avoid s and CSS variables
- Minimize use of `!important`; keep specificity low
- Prioritize utility and component classes over custom CSS
- Use consistent units (rem, logical properties) and naming conventions
- Document dynamic utilities and complex variants

# Theme colors
- Use semantic names (`primary`, `secondary`) with light/dark suffixes
- Adopt modern P3 color palette exposed as CSS variables
- Apply opacity modifiers (`/50`) or `color-mix` when appropriate
- Leveraapt to system preferences

# Typography
- Use theme font sizes (`text-sm`…`text-6xl`), weights, and line heights
- Employ `font-stretch-*` utilities for variable-font tuning
- Maintain accessible heading hierarchy and consistent prose styles

